Eragrostis lehmanniana

   [5738.jpg]
   Authority Nees
   Family Liliopsida:Commelinidae:Cyperales:Gramineae
   Synonyms Eragrostis chaunantha Nees, Eragrostis vansonii Bremek. &
   Oberm.
   Common names Lehmann's love grass, knietjiesgras
   Editor
   Ecocrop code 5738

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A hardy, branched, tufted grass with 60-90 cm tall
   culms. USES Used for pasture but should not be grazed before well
   established and should not be grazed to closely. Also used for erosion
   control. In Africa, it is used as a remedy for colic, diarrhea, and
   typhoid fever. GROWING PERIOD Perennial or annual grass growing spring
   to autumn. COMMON NAMES Lehmann love grass. FURTHER INF Lehmann love
   grass is native of South Africa. In southern California it is found at
   elevations between sea level and 1700 m, but it is best grown at
   1000-1500 m.

   Sources
   [10]Grassland Index
   Skerman P 1990 pp 422-424 [KTMP, RAIN, TEXT, PH, PHO]
   Duke J 1979 pp 95 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]
   Duke J 1975 pp 16 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 76 [USE]
   Heath M 1985 pp 1983 PP 183 [RAIN]
   IBPGR 1984 pp 181

